<%= content_for :title do %>
  Create a blog with a built-in email newsletter
<% end %>

<%= content_for :og_image do %>
  <%= dynamic_og_image_for_landing_page(title: "A Newsletter Should Start as a Post, Not a Campaign") %>
<% end %>

<%= content_for :meta_description do %>
  Pagecord is a blog with built-in email subscriptions. Publish posts to your site and send them to subscribers per post or as an automatic weekly digest.
<% end %>

<div class="md:mt-4 mb-4 md:mb-8 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4">
  <h1 class="source-serif font-semibold text-center text-4xl md:text-6xl tracking-tight text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200">
    A newsletter should start as a post, not a campaign.
  </h1>

  <div class="md:text-xl text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 flex flex-col gap-y-4 mt-8 md:mt-12">
    <p>
      Newsletter tools are built for marketing departments: campaigns, templates, segments, drip sequences, conversion funnels, and constant list anxiety.
    </p>
    <p>
      Most independent writers need something calmer. Write a post. Publish it to your site. Let readers get it by email if that is how they prefer to follow along.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pagecord is a blog first, with email subscriptions built in. Send individual posts when they matter, or let Pagecord send a weekly digest automatically.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="text-center mt-8 mb-4 md:text-xl">
    <%= link_to new_signup_path do %>
      <div class="mt-2 inline-flex font-medium p-4 rounded-xl shadow-sm btn-primary text-xl">Start free</div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render "comparison_intro", sections: [
  {
    title: "Who this is for",
    paragraphs: [
      "Writers, creators, consultants, tiny teams, and personal bloggers who want readers to subscribe without turning the whole site into a newsletter business.",
      "It is for people who want a public archive, RSS, a custom domain, and email delivery from the same place."
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "Why a blog comes first",
    paragraphs: [
      "Email is excellent for reaching people, but a newsletter alone can make your writing feel temporary. It lands in an inbox, ages quickly, and is hard to browse later.",
      "A blog gives every piece a home: a URL, an archive, search visibility, links from other sites, and a place readers can return to."
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "What Pagecord does differently",
    paragraphs: [
      "Pagecord sends posts to subscribers without asking you to design a campaign. Choose per-post delivery for important updates or weekly digest mode for a quieter rhythm.",
      "Subscribers are attached to your site, not a separate newsletter machine. Your writing stays readable on the open web."
    ]
  }
] %>

<%= render "screenshots" %>

<div class="md:mt-4 mb-4 md:mb-8 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4">
  <section class="my-10 md:my-14 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8">
    <h2 class="source-serif font-semibold text-3xl md:text-4xl tracking-tight text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200">Good writing deserves a home</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 md:text-xl text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 flex flex-col gap-y-4">
      <p>
        A newsletter platform makes the inbox the destination. Pagecord makes your site the destination, then uses email as a friendly way back to it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Classic is free forever. Premium is $<%= localised_price %>/year and includes email subscriptions, custom domains, analytics, image uploads, and more.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<%= render "landing_examples",
  examples: [
    { name: "Chad Moore", url: "https://blog.chadmoore.net/", description: "A personal blog with a custom domain and a natural rhythm for reader updates." },
    { name: "Moonwriting", url: "https://moonwriting.blog", description: "A writer-owned site where posts can be followed without needing a separate newsletter platform." },
    { name: "Focustivity", url: "https://focustivity.blog", description: "A personal site that can publish posts and keep subscribers in the loop." }
  ],
  testimonials: [
    { name: "Greg", url: "https://iamgregb.io/", quote: "Pagecord is the perfect place to host your own blog, especially if you want to keep things simple without getting lost in modern publishing platforms or newsletter engines." },
    { name: "Eetu", url: "https://moonwriting.blog", quote: "Pagecord has everything I'm looking for. Open source, privacy-respecting, with many customization options. Pricing is competitive." }
  ] %>
